body:
@sschepens No problem. The only tricky part is that there might be some admin call that are taking ~30sec. For example, when unloading a namespace that has many (thousands of) topics, it can take ~10sec. 

Also, some of the REST calls (eg: clearing backlog on whole namespace) are actually generating multiple internal REST calls (eg: one per bundle) and that can add up to the total time. 

That's why I'm a bit worried about the 30sec :) . In any case, I totally agree we need to have a max on it.

> Are we controlling the logger object destruction?

Yeah, that's my suspicion as well. 

@jai1  Have you ran this through valgrind? That should give a hint, irrespectively on whether it crashes or not.
